dcterms:description: The IcePaHC corpus is a Penn-style treebank that is lemmatised, part-of-speech tagged, and annotated for constituent structure, containing approximately 1,000,000 words from 61 text extracts spanning 10 centuries (1150-2008).
dcterms:title: IcePaHC (Icelandic Parsed Historical Corpus)

dcterms:description: The Penn Treebank is a large annotated corpus of English that provides a syntactically annotated dataset for various linguistic analyses.
